{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0beb8aac-82c9-4dd3-abd5-57c057687c54","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nThen run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nReview the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for any API or behavioral changes, and update NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7b0e1d2c-f36e-45cc-8542-ddae5213c655","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore.","outputTokens":297,"requestId":"3018:37A40F:161F462:18E269F:6A067B6B"},"id":"d9a03c07-9843-450c-b2fd-d8aebe8301fe","timestamp":"2026-05-15T01:48:33.368Z","parentId":"180463d5-4815-470f-aa38-1b4fc60e1dba"}
